President Biden addressed a teleconference call with Atlanta Mayor Keisha Lance Bottoms, expressing gratitude for her support and leadership. He commended her for standing strong during challenging times, such as the recent mass shooting in Atlanta and the protests last summer. President Biden highlighted the importance of democracy and the need to make government work for working families. He discussed the impact of the American Rescue Plan, including the distribution of COVID-19 vaccines and direct payments to Americans. The plan also aims to reduce child poverty, invest in education, expand Medicaid coverage, and provide financial support to local governments. President Biden emphasized his vision for a Build Back Better plan, focusing on infrastructure, research and development, job creation, and support for historically Black colleges and universities. He closed by urging unity and advocating for science, justice, equality, and voting rights.